    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1887-02-01T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1887-02-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="463"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d463">
                <head>No. 8.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Sir <persName type="from">L. S. Sackville West</persName> to
                        Mr. <persName type="to">Bayard</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">British Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1887-02-01">
                            <hi rend="italic">February</hi> 1, 1887</date>. (Received February
                        2.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With reference to your note of the 12th ultimo, I
                    have the honor to inform you that under date of the 27th ultimo the Marquis of
                    Salisbury <pb facs="0794" n="1752" xml:id="pg_1752"/> instructs me to inquire
                    whether the inform and papers reia tive to the seizure of the British schooners
                        <hi rend="italic">Carolena, Onward</hi>, and <hi rend="italic">Thornton</hi>
                    have reached the United States Government.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">L. S. Sackville West.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
